# Project Structure & Organization

## Folder Layout (Feature-Based)

```
frontend/src/
├── assets/               # Static files (images, fonts)
├── common/
│   ├── components/       # Shared UI used in 2+ features
│   ├── hooks/            # Shared hooks (useLocalStorage, useDebounce)
│   └── utils/            # Shared utility functions
├── config/               # External service integrations only
├── constants/            # App-wide constants used in 2+ features
├── contexts/             # AuthContext, LanguageContext (app-wide)
├── layouts/              # Sidebar, Header, page shells
├── pages/
│   └── {feature}/
│       ├── components/   # Feature-specific UI
│       ├── hooks/        # Feature-specific hooks
│       ├── types.ts      # Feature-specific types
│       ├── {Feature}.tsx # Page root component
│       └── index.ts      # Barrel export
├── services/             # API call functions
├── store/                # Global state stores
├── types/                # Global shared TypeScript types
└── App.tsx
```

## Rules

- Widgets belong in `pages/dashboard/widgets/`, not a top-level `widgets/` folder
- Auth pages/components belong in `pages/auth/`
- If a component/hook is used in only ONE feature → keep it inside that feature folder
- If used in 2+ features → move to `common/`
- Every page folder must have an `index.ts` barrel export

## Backend Layout (Layered Architecture)

```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── api/v1/endpoints/ # Route handlers (HTTP logic only)
│   ├── core/             # config.py, logging.py
│   ├── schemas/          # Pydantic request/response models
│   └── services/         # Business logic
├── tests/
├── main.py               # App factory, CORS, router mounting
└── pyproject.toml
```

- Routers handle HTTP only — parse request, call service, return response
- Services hold all business logic — no FastAPI imports
- Schemas hold all Pydantic models — no business logic

## Tooling

- Frontend: ESLint + Prettier (`singleQuote: true`, `semi: false`, `printWidth: 100`)
- Backend: Black (line-length 88) + Ruff for linting
